# sentence_id = 4
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 1.4
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = For just as some people represent many things by portraying them with colors and forms—some through art and others through habit—and others again through the voice; so also in the arts mentioned above, all produce the imitation in rhythm, language, and harmony, either used separately or mixed together.
# literal_translation = Just-as for and with-colors and with-shapes many-things they-imitate some portraying (the some through art the others through habit), others but through the voice, so also-in the mentioned arts all indeed they-make the imitation in rhythm and language and harmony, with-these but either separately or having-been-mixed.
