# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = There are some arts which use all the means mentioned—I mean rhythm, melody, and meter—such as dithyrambic and nomic poetry, and tragedy and comedy. They differ because some use them all at once and others in different parts.
# literal_translation = Are but some [arts] which all use the having-been-mentioned, I-speak but for-example rhythm and melody and meter, just-as the of-the dithyrambic poetry and the of-the nomes and tragedy and comedy; they-differ but because the indeed at-once all the but according-to part.
