# sentence_id = 25
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 3.4
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = So that in one respect Sophocles would be the same kind of imitator as Homer, for both imitate noble men, but in another respect the same as Aristophanes, for both imitate men acting and doing. Hence some say they are called "dramas," because they imitate those doing.
# literal_translation = So-that in-the indeed the same would be imitator to-Homer Sophocles, they-imitate for both noble-ones, in-the but to-Aristophanes, acting for they-imitate and doing both. Whence also dramas to-be-called some them they-say, because they-imitate doing-ones.
