# sentence_id = 26
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 3.5
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = This is why the Dorians lay claim to both tragedy and comedy (for the Megarians here claim comedy as originating during their democracy, and those in Sicily as well, since the poet Epicharmus was from there and lived much earlier than Chionides and Magnes; and some of those in the Peloponnese claim tragedy), using these names as evidence.
# literal_translation = Wherefore also they-claim-for-themselves the both tragedy and the comedy the Dorians (the indeed for comedy the Megarians the-ones here as during the among them democracy having-become and the-ones from Sicily, from-there for was Epicharmus the poet by-much earlier being of-Chionides and of-Magnes; and of-the tragedy some the-ones in Peloponnese) making the names evidence;
