# sentence_id = 68
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 6.2
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Tragedy, then, is an imitation of an action that is serious, complete, and of a certain magnitude; in language embellished with each kind of artistic ornament, the several kinds being found in separate parts of the play; in the form of action, not of narrative; through pity and fear effecting the proper purgation of these emotions.
# literal_translation = Is therefore tragedy imitation of-action serious and complete magnitude having, with-embellished language separately for-each of-the forms in the parts, of-persons-acting and not through narrative, through pity and fear effecting the of-the such sufferings purgation.
