# prose_translation = But the limit fixed by the nature of the case is this: the greater the size, the more beautiful it will be, provided it remains clear. As a general rule, a sufficient limit of magnitude is that within which a sequence of events occurring according to probability or necessity results in a change from bad fortune to good, or from good to bad.
# literal_translation = the but according-to itself the nature of-the thing definition, always indeed the greater until of-the clear to-be more-beautiful is according-to the magnitude; as but simply having-determined to-speak, in as-much magnitude according-to the likely or the necessary in-sequence of-becoming it-happens into happiness from misfortune or from happiness into misfortune to-change, sufficient definition is of-the magnitude.
