# sentence_id = 112
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 9.2
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = The poet and the historian differ not by writing in verse or in prose. The work of Herodotus might be put into verse, and it would still be history with meter, no less than without it. The true difference is that one relates what has happened, the other what may happen.
# literal_translation = The for historian and the poet not in-the either in-meter to-speak or without-meter differ (might for would the of-Herodotus into meters to-be-placed and nothing less would be history certain with meter or without meters); but in-this differs, in-the the indeed the things-having-happened to-speak, the but of-what-sort might become.
