# sentence_id = 116
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 9.6
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = In the case of Tragedy, they cling to historical names. The reason is that what is possible is persuasive; what has not happened we do not yet believe to be possible, but what has happened is evidently possible, for it would not have happened if it were impossible.
# literal_translation = Upon but of-the tragedy of-the things-having-happened names they-cling. Cause but that persuasive is the possible; the indeed therefore not things-having-happened not-yet we-believe to-be possible, the but things-having-happened manifest that possible; not for would have-happened, if was impossible.
