# sentence_id = 117
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 9.7
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Nevertheless, even in tragedies, in some cases only one or two of the well-known names are used, while the others are invented; in some, no well-known names are used at all, as in Agathon’s Antheus. For in this play both the incidents and the names are invented, and it gives no less pleasure.
# literal_translation = Not however but and in the tragedies in some indeed one or two of-the well-known is of-names, the but other having-been-made, in some but none, such-as in the of-Agathon Antheus; similarly for in this both the things and the names has-been-made, and nothing less it-pleases.
