# prose_translation = For the element of wonder will be enhanced if events occur in this way, rather than by chance or at random. For even among chance occurrences, those seem most wonderful that appear to have happened as it were by design; as for instance when the statue of Mitys at Argos fell upon the man responsible for Mitys' death and killed him while he was watching a festival. For such things do not seem likely to occur by mere chance.
# literal_translation = the for wonderful so will-hold more than if from of-the automatic and of-the fortune, since also of-the from fortune these most-wonderful seem as-many-as just-as on-purpose appears to-have-become, such-as as the statue the of-the Mitys in Argos killed the cause of-the death to-the Mitys, watching having-fallen-in; it-seems for the such not at-random to-become;
