# prose_translation = nor again should the extremely wicked man fall from fortune to misfortune; for such a structure might have human appeal but would not have pity or fear, for the one [pity] is concerned with the man suffering undeservedly, the other [fear] with the one who is like us—pity for the undeserving, fear for the like—so the result will be neither pitiable nor fearful.
