# prose_translation = There remains, then, the person between these. Such is the man who does not excel in virtue and justice, nor does he change to misfortune through vice and depravity, but through some error, being one of those in great reputation and fortune, such as Oedipus and Thyestes and the famous men of such families.
# literal_translation = The between then of these remaining . Is but such the neither in virtue excelling and in justice nor through vice and depravity changing into the misfortune but through error certain , of the in great reputation being and in good-fortune , such-as Oedipus and Thyestes and the from the such families distinguished men .
