# sentence_id = 154
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 13.7
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = This is confirmed by what has actually happened; for whereas at first the poets used to take any story at random, nowadays the finest tragedies are composed about a few houses—for example, about Alcmeon, Oedipus, Orestes, Meleager, Thyestes, Telephus, and any others who have happened to suffer or to do terrible things.
# literal_translation = Sign but and the happening ; first on-the-one-hand for the poets the random plots used-to-enumerate , now but concerning few houses the best tragedies are-composed , such-as concerning Alcmeon and Oedipus and Orestes and Meleager and Thyestes and Telephus and as-many-as to-others it-happened either to-suffer terrible-things or to-do .
