# sentence_id = 173
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 14.13
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Alternatively, the terrible deed may be performed by those in ignorance of who the victim is, and the friendship discovered later, as in Sophocles’ Oedipus; in that play, the deed is outside the drama, but within the tragedy itself we have examples like Astydamas’ Alcmeon or Telegonus in The Wounded Odysseus.
# literal_translation = Is but to-do on-the-one-hand , being-ignorant but to-do the terrible-deed , then later to-discover the friendship , just-as the of-Sophocles Oedipus ; this on-the-one-hand therefore outside of-the drama , in but itself the tragedy such-as the Alcmeon the of-Astydamas or the Telegonus the in the wounded Odysseus .
