# subdoc = 14.16
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Of these, to be about to do the deed with full knowledge and then not do it is the worst; for it is repulsive and not tragic, since there is no suffering. Therefore no one does this except rarely, as for instance Haemon with Creon in the Antigone.
