# sentence_id = 179
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 14.19
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = The best is the last case—I mean as in the Cresphontes where Merope is about to kill her son, but does not, but recognizes him; and in the Iphigenia where the sister recognizes her brother; and in the Helle where the son, about to give up his mother, recognizes her.
# literal_translation = Best but the last , I-say but such-as in the Cresphontes the Merope is-about the son to-kill , kills but not , but recognized , and in the Iphigenia the sister the brother , and in the Helle the son the mother giving-up being-about recognized .
