# sentence_id = 206
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 16.10
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = There is also a composite kind based on a false inference of the audience, as in Odysseus the False Messenger; for the fact that he could bend the bow, and no one else could, is a fabrication by the poet and a premise, even if he said he would recognize the bow which he had not seen; but to make it happen as if he would be recognized by that means is a false inference.
# literal_translation = Is but certain and composite from of-paralogism of-the theater , such-as in the Odysseus to-the false-messenger ; the on-the-one-hand for the bow to-bend , other but no-one , having-been-made by of-the poet and premise , and if at-any-rate the bow he-said to-be-about-to-know which not he-had-seen ; the but as through of-that he-would-recognize through of-this to-make paralogism .
