# sentence_id = 207
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 16.11
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = But the best recognition of all is that which arises from the events themselves, when the startling effect comes about through probable means, as in Sophocles’ Oedipus and the Iphigenia; for it is probable that she would want to give someone a letter. For such recognitions alone occur without manufactured signs and necklaces.
# literal_translation = of-all but best recognition the from of-themselves of-the things , of-the startling-effect becoming through of-likely-means , such-as in the of-Sophocles Oedipus and the Iphigenia ; likely for to-wish to-place-upon letters . the for such-ones alone without of-the having-been-made signs and necklaces .
