# sentence_id = 214
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 17.6
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = I mean that the general outline might be viewed in this way, for example in the Iphigenia: a certain girl having been offered for sacrifice and vanished in a way unknown to those who sacrificed her, and having been settled in another land where it was the custom to sacrifice strangers to the goddess, she held this priesthood; after some time it happened that the brother of the priestess came there (the fact that the god commanded him to come for some reason outside the general plot, and for what purpose, is outside the myth); but having come and being captured, when he was about to be sacrificed he made himself known—either as Euripides or as Polyidus made it happen, saying in a natural way that not only his sister but he himself also had to be sacrificed—and from this came his salvation.
# literal_translation = I say but thus would to be viewed the generally , such as of the Iphigenia ; having been sacrificed certain girl and having been vanished unknown to the having sacrificed , having been settled but into another land , in which law was the strangers to sacrifice to the goddess , this she held the priesthood ; with time but later to the brother it happened to come of the priestess , the but that commanded the god through some cause outside of the general to come there and for what but outside of the myth ; having come but and having been taken to be sacrificed being about he recognized , either as Euripides or as Polyidus did , according to the likely having said that not therefore only the sister but also himself it behooved to be sacrificed , and from thence the salvation .
