# sentence_id = 247
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 19.8
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = No criticism can be leveled against the art of poetry on account of the poet's knowledge or ignorance of these things that is at all worth serious consideration. For why should one suppose it a mistake, as Protagoras did, that when the poet thinks he is praying, he actually commands when he says, "Sing, goddess, the wrath"? For to bid someone to do or not do something is, he says, a command.
# literal_translation = Beside for the of-these knowledge or ignorance nothing into the poetic criticism is-brought what and worthy of-zeal . What for would-one-take to-have-been-erred which Protagoras reproaches , that to-pray thinking he-commands having-said " wrath sing goddess " ; the for to-bid , he-says , to-do something or not command is .
