# prose_translation = Its subdivisions are: vowel, semivowel, and mute. A vowel is a letter which has an audible sound without any impact (of tongue or lips); a semivowel, one which has an audible sound with such impact, for example S and R; a mute, one which with such impact has no sound of its own, but becomes audible when combined with letters that have a sound, for example G and D.
# literal_translation = of-this but parts both the vowel and the semivowel and mute . is but these vowel on the one hand the without impact having sound audible , semivowel but the with impact having sound audible , such-as the S and the R , mute but the with impact by itself on the one hand none having sound , with but of-the having some sound becoming audible , such-as the G and the D .
