# prose_translation = and sometimes they add the term to which the thing replaced is related. I mean, for example, a cup is related to Dionysus as a shield is to Ares; he will therefore call the cup "the shield of Dionysus" and the shield "the cup of Ares."
# literal_translation = and sometimes they-add instead of-which it-says towards what it-is . I-say but such-as similarly has cup towards Dionysus and shield towards Ares ; he-will-say therefore the cup shield of-Dionysus and the shield cup of-Ares .
