# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = In some cases there is no established name for the analogical term, but it will be expressed analogically nonetheless; for instance, to scatter seed is to sow, but the scattering of flame from the sun is nameless; yet this process has the same relation to the sun as sowing has to the seed, hence the expression "sowing the god-created flame."
# literal_translation = to-some but not is name lying of-the analogy , but nothing less similarly it-will-be-said ; such-as the the fruit on-the-one-hand to-send-forth to-sow , the but the flame from of-the sun nameless ; but similarly has this towards the sun and the to-sow towards the fruit , through-which it-has-been-said sowing god-created flame .
