# prose_translation = Furthermore, Ariphrades used to ridicule the tragedians because they use expressions which no one would ever use in conversation, such as "domatōn apo" instead of "apo domatōn," and "sethen," and "egō de nin," and "Achilleōs peri" instead of "peri Achilleōs," and all other such terms.
# literal_translation = further but Ariphrades the tragedians ridiculed that which no-one would say in the dialect these they-use , such-as the from-houses-away but not away from-houses , and the thy , and the I but him , and the of-Achilles concerning but not concerning of-Achilles , and as-many-as others such .
