# sentence_id = 312
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 23.5
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = In this respect, then, as we have already said, Homer would appear marvelous compared to the others, since he did not attempt to make even the Trojan War a single whole, despite its having a beginning and an end; for the plot would have been likely to be too large and not easily viewed as a whole, or if moderated in size, to be entangled by its variety. As it is, he takes one part and uses many episodes from the rest, for example the Catalogue of Ships and other episodes with which he breaks up his poetry.
# literal_translation = through-which just-as we-said already and in-this marvelous would appear Homer beside the others , the neither the war although having beginning and end to-attempt to-make whole ; too for would great and not easily-viewed was-likely to-be the myth , or with-the magnitude being-moderate having-been-entangled with-the variety . now but one part having-taken with-episodes has-used of-them many , such-as of-ships catalogue and with-others episodes twice he-breaks-up the poetry .
