# sentence_id = 314
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 23.7
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Consequently, while out of the Iliad and Odyssey only one tragedy or at most two are made from each, many are made from the Cypria and more than eight from the Little Iliad: for instance, the Judgment of Arms, Philoctetes, Neoptolemus, Eurypylus, the Beggary, the Laconian Women, the Destruction of Ilium, the Sailing Away, Sinon, and the Trojan Women.
# literal_translation = consequently from on-the-one-hand Iliad and Odyssey one tragedy is-made of-each or two only , from but Cyprian-poems many and of-the Little Iliad more eight , such as of-arms judgment , Philoctetes , Neoptolemus , Eurypylus , beggary , Laconian Women , of-Ilium destruction and sailing away and Sinon and Trojan Women .
