# prose_translation = Furthermore, the thought and the diction must be good. Homer used all these elements both first and sufficiently. For each of his poems is constructed differently: the Iliad is simple and full of suffering, the Odyssey complex (for recognition occurs throughout) and ethical; moreover, he has surpassed all in diction and thought.
# literal_translation = Further the thoughts and the diction to have well. [In] which all Homer has used both first and sufficiently. And for of the poems each has been composed the on the one hand Iliad simple and full-of-suffering, the on the other hand Odyssey complex (recognition for throughout) and ethical; toward but these in diction and in thought all he has surpassed.
