# sentence_id = 320
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 24.6
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Epic poetry has a special property for extending its size, because in tragedy it is not possible to imitate many parts of the action happening at once, but only the part on the stage involving the actors. In epic, because it is narrative, it is possible to represent many parts as being carried out simultaneously, and if these are relevant, the bulk of the poem is increased.
# literal_translation = It-has but toward the to-be-extended the size much something the epic-poetry peculiar through the in on-the-one-hand the tragedy not to-be-possible together being-acted many parts to-imitate but the upon the stage and of-the actors part only; in but the epic-poetry through the narrative to-be it-is-possible many parts together to-make being-finished, by of-which belonging being it-is-increased the of-the poem bulk.
