# subdoc = 25.21
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Others by usage of diction. They call wine mixed with water 'wine', whence it is written 'greave of newly-wrought tin'; and they call 'braziers' those who work iron, whence Ganymede is said 'to pour wine for Zeus', though they do not drink wine. This might also be metaphorical.
# literal_translation = The but according-to the habit of-the diction. The mixed wine they-say to-be, whence it-has-been-made «greave of-newly-wrought of-tin»; and braziers the the iron working, whence it-has-been-said the Ganymede for-Zeus to-pour-wine, not drinking wine. It-might-be and-would this-at-least also according-to metaphor.
