# subdoc = 25.25
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = This has happened in the case of Icarius. People think he was a Laconian; it is therefore absurd, they say, that Telemachus did not meet him when he went to Lacedaemon. But perhaps it is as the Cephallenians say; for they say that Odysseus married from their people and that the name was Icadius, not Icarius. So it is likely that the problem arises from a mistake.
# literal_translation = This but has-suffered the concerning Icarius. They-think for him Laconian to-be; absurd therefore the not to-meet the Telemachus him into Lacedaemon having-come. The but perhaps holds just-as the Cephallenians they-say; from of-them for to-marry they-say the Odysseus and to-be Icadius but not Icarius; through error but the problem † likely is †.
